<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Variation of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. from across their range. Top two rows, males; bottom row females; holotype male top left." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717524" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Dorsal habitus photographs of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (left) and female (right). Scale bars: 10 mm, silhouettes to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717525" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Ventral habitus photographs of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (left) and female (right). Scale bars: 10 mm, silhouettes to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717526" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure4>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Carapace of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (left) and paratype female (right). Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717527" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure5>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Carapace (upper) and sternopectinal region (lower) of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (left) and female (right). Taken under ultraviolet illumination. Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717528" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure6>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Pedipalp of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov., holotype male (above) and female (below). Macrosetae indicated with open circles (proximal) and closed circles (diagnosis character 4). Carinae abbreviations: retrolateral median (rm), dorsal retrolateral (drl), dorsal median (dm), dorsal prolateral (dpl), ventral retrolateral (vrl), ventral prosubmedian (vps), prolateral ventral (plv), prolateral median (plm). Scale bars: 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717529" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Illustrations of pedipalp chela of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. A-D holotype male and E-H female A, E retrolateral B, F prolateral C, G dorsal D, H ventral. Trichobothria indicated with open circles. Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717530" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Illustrations of pedipalp patella and femur of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (B, C) paratype female (A, D). A dorsal patella B retrolateral patella C ventral patella D dorsal femur. Trichobothria indicated with open circles. Scale bars: 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717531" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure9>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Metasoma of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. holotype male (above) and female (below); ventral, lateral, and dorsal aspects (top to bottom). Ventral sub-median, ventrolateral, lateral submedian, and dorsolateral macrosetae on segments I-IV indicated with black circles (diagnosis character 3). Carinae abbreviations: Dorsolateral (dl), lateral median (lm), lateral supramedian (lsm), lateral inframedian (lim), ventrolateral (vm), ventral submedian (vs), and ventromedian (vm). Scale bars: 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717532" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Right hemispermatophore of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov.: anterior aspect (left) and posterior aspect (right). Scale bar: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717533" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure11>
    dc:description "Figure 11. Soda Lake and the surrounding Carrizo Plain, the type locality of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. Above, satellite imagery of the central Carrizo Plain taken in June 2019; below, a regional overview taken from the eastern side of the North Basin and facing southwest across the Soda Lake taken in May 2021." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717534" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure12>
    dc:description "Figure 12. Habitat of Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. in May 2021. Note the dominance of Allenrolfea occidentalis and the soft, exposed clay soil along the lakebed." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717535" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure13>
    dc:description "Figure 13. Photographs of a typical juvenile Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. (left), and atypical coloration observed in one late instar juvenile female. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717536" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1117.76872.figure14>
    dc:description "Figure 14. Adult female Paruroctonus soda sp. nov. with 51 newly born juveniles." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717537" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

